<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-02-17T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-02-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="584" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">819.51/366: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">South</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-02-17T11:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 17,
                                        1923—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8:33
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>14. My despatch no. 192, January 15th.<note n="33" xml:id="d584fn33">Not
                                printed.</note> President yesterday approved bill authorizing loan
                            up to $4,500,000 for road building purposes. Section providing for
                            withdrawal from the United States of six-million-dollar fund
                            eliminated.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">South</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>